Hello! Welcome to the Inspired Square Privacy Policy. This policy explains how Inspired Square collects, uses, processes, and shares information about you.
This Privacy Policy applies to your download, access, and/or use of Inspired Square Games, whether on your computer, mobile device, or any other platform (each a "Game" and together the “Games”). It also covers our Marketing and Advertising activities on all platforms and other Services we may provide, including campaigns with influencers. This Privacy Policy also applies to any other Services we may provide related to our Games or Website, such as customer support, social media, community channels, and other websites we may operate from time to time. We refer to all our Games and Services collectively as our "Services."
When you download, access, and/or play our Games, or interact with our Websites or other Services, you acknowledge the collection and use of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy, including Inspired Square’s and our advertising partners’ use of your data for targeted advertising purposes as described in the Marketing and Advertising sections of this Privacy Policy. Those sections also explain how you can opt in or out of the use of your personal information for targeted advertising purposes. If you have any concerns about providing information to us or how it is used as described in this Privacy Policy, you should not use our Games or other Services.
Playing Our Games
When you download, access, and/or play our Games or use our other Services, we collect information about you. Most of this information comes directly from you or your device, such as device information, country, region, and gameplay information. We use this information to provide our Games and Services to you, including for optimization, fraud prevention, customizing in-game offers, and verifying purchases. We will also use it for other purposes set out in this Privacy Policy, including Marketing and Advertising.
Visiting Our Websites
When you visit our Websites, such as
inspiredsquare.com
, and other Websites operated by us (“Websites”), we may collect information about you, such as details about how you use and interact with such Websites. We may use this information for various purposes, including operating and optimizing the Websites, in connection with our advertising purposes, and for research or analysis.
Inspired Square Profile and Playing Socially
You can choose to use a third-party social network (such as Facebook or Google Sign in) to add information to your Inspired Square Profile or to connect to your account. If you do this, then your personal information will be visible to other players, and we’ll also use it for other purposes set out in this Privacy Policy, including Marketing and Advertising.
Marketing
Where we record your preferences permitting us to do so (see further below on how to change your preferences), we and our third-party partners use information collected about you to send you marketing communications about our Games and other Services based on your interests. For example, we may send emails, serve ads within our Services, or place ads on third-party websites, apps, and Internet-connected devices.
We will use the information we hold about you to promote our Games and other Services in various ways, including:
Advertising within third-party websites, apps, and Internet-connected devices
Showing you promotions for other Inspired Square or its Group Companies’ games in the Games you play
Advertising
Our Games include advertising for third-party products and services.
Inspired Square and our advertising partners collect and use information about you to improve advertising, targeting, and measurement systems so that we can show you relevant third-party ads in our Games.
Inspired Square participates in the IAB Europe Transparency & Consent Framework and complies with its Specifications and Policies. Inspired Square uses the Consent Management Platform (CMP).
Where applicable, we use a CMP to gather consent and permissions for our advertising-based activity. Where local laws allow, we will opt you into targeted advertising by default. You can change your preferences at any time in the Privacy and Security settings of our Games.
Ad Identifiers, Cookies, and Similar Technologies
To provide our Games, other Services, Websites, and targeted advertising, we use ad identifiers, cookies, and similar technologies. This section describes our use of these technologies and how you can manage your preferences.
Crash Logs Data
When you use our Games and Services, we may collect crash logs and other data related to technical issues and performance. This information helps us understand and resolve issues that occur during gameplay and improve the overall user experience. The crash logs data we collect includes the following:
Crash Logs:
Detailed reports of any crashes or errors that occur while you are using our Games and Services. These logs may include information about your device, operating system, game version, and the specific circumstances under which the crash occurred.
Analytics:
Data on how you interact with our Games and Services, such as gameplay statistics, in-game events, and usage patterns. This information helps us analyze and understand player behavior, optimize game performance, and enhance user satisfaction.
Purpose of Collecting Crash Logs Data
The primary purposes of collecting crash logs and analytics data are as follows:
Issue Resolution:
To identify, diagnose, and fix bugs, crashes, and other technical issues that may arise during gameplay. This helps us ensure that our Games and Services run smoothly and reliably.
Performance Optimization:
To analyze the performance of our Games and Services and make necessary improvements. This includes optimizing load times, reducing crashes, and enhancing the overall gaming experience.
User Experience Enhancement:
To understand how players interact with our Games and Services, allowing us to make informed decisions about game design, features, and updates that enhance user satisfaction.
Security and Fraud Prevention:
To detect and prevent security threats, cheating, and other malicious activities that may compromise the integrity of our Games and Services.
How We Use Crash Logs Data
We use crash logs and analytics data in the following ways:
Technical Support:
To provide effective customer support by quickly identifying and addressing technical issues reported by players.
Development and Testing:
To inform our development and testing processes, ensuring that new updates and features are thoroughly vetted and free of critical issues.
Continuous Improvement:
To continuously improve the quality and performance of our Games and Services based on real-world usage data and feedback.
Reporting and Insights:
To generate reports and insights that help us understand trends, usage patterns, and areas for improvement.
By collecting and analyzing crash logs and analytics data, we aim to deliver a more reliable, enjoyable, and secure gaming experience for all our players. If you have any questions or concerns about our data collection practices, please contact us at
support@inspiredsquare.com
.
Your Rights
You have the right to know whether your personal data is shared with third parties.
Right to Know:
You can request information about the categories and specific pieces of personal data we have collected, used and disclosed.
Right to Delete:
You can request the deletion of your personal data.
Right to Opt-Out:
Users have the right to opt out of targeted advertising/sharing of data. Opting out means users may still see non-personalized ads. Since we do not sell users' data to anyone, no options are available for opting out of data sales. If users have any queries, they can contact us at support@inspiredsquare.com.
Right to Rectify:
You can request corrections to any inaccuracies in your personal data.
Right to Request Correction of Personal Data:
Users can request the correction of inaccuracies in their personal data. Contact the Data Protection Officer at
dataprotectionofficer@inspiredsquare.com
to make a request. Verification of identity is required before making corrections. This right is provided under relevant laws, including GDPR and CCPA. Personal data will be updated within a specified timeframe (e.g., 30 days) of receiving a valid request. If a request cannot be fulfilled, an explanation will be provided.
Right to Anonymize, Block, or Delete:
Request anonymization, blocking, or deletion of unnecessary or excessive data or data processed in non-compliance with the LGPD.
Right to Lodge a Complaint to the Supervisory Authority (EEA/UK/Canada):
We aim to address any questions or concerns you may have regarding our processing of your personal information. If you would like to discuss any issues, please contact us using the details provided below. However, if your concerns remain unresolved, you have the right to lodge a complaint with data protection authorities. You can file your complaint in your province, country, or member state of residence, your place of work, or where you believe a data protection law infringement occurred.
Residents of certain US states also have the option to appoint an agent to exercise their rights as outlined above. We will take measures to verify the identity of the person making the request and to confirm that the agent has been authorized to act on your behalf by requiring a signed written authorization or a copy of a power of attorney.
Exercising Your Rights
Request Information, Deletion, or Rectification:
Visit Privacy Settings inside the Game or contact us directly at
support@inspiredsquare.com
.
Opt-Out of Targeted Advertising/Sharing or Data Sale:
Users can adjust their settings to control their personal information for targeted advertising and sharing of data. They can disconnect social media accounts, delete our games, limit ad tracking in phone settings, or prevent cookies in web browsers. As we previously mentioned, we do not sell any of users' data, so no options are available for opting out of data sales. For any queries, please contact us directly at support@inspiredsquare.com.
Detailed Information on Data Sharing:
Review our privacy policy or contact us directly at
support@inspiredsquare.com
.
Contact Information
For any issues or to exercise your rights, contact us at:
support@inspiredsquare.com
. Additional information and requests can be managed via the Data Deletion form available at:
https://inspiredsquare.com/datadeletion/datadeletion.html
. We respond to all data protection requests we receive in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
Children
You must be over a certain age to play our Games and use our Services, depending on where you live. We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from or direct or target interest-based advertising to anyone under the ages set out below or under 16 for California residents, nor knowingly allow such persons to use our Games and Services. If you believe we might have any information from or about a child under the age set out below, please contact us.
General
This Privacy Policy contains further details about:
Who we share your information with and the reasons for sharing it
Measures we take to keep your information secure
The legal basis under which we process your information
How long we retain your information and where we store it
When and why we share your information with third parties, including transfers outside of the European Economic Area (the “EEA”), the UK, Switzerland, and Canada (including Quebec)
Changes or updates to our Privacy Policy
US Residents
In addition to the information provided throughout this Privacy Policy, state privacy laws in the United States require that we disclose to consumers in those states additional information about the processing of their personal information. Below we describe the purposes for which we use and disclose personal information and, for each purpose, the categories of personal information we use and disclose, and the categories of third parties to whom we disclose the personal information.
Service Functionality
We use certain information to provide you with our Services, including to create and manage your account, enter a contract for sale or services, facilitate purchases or process payments, fulfill orders, send service communications, provide customer service functions, and conduct general business operations, such as accounting, recordkeeping, and audits, analyzing our performance, and meeting our legal obligations.
Service Improvement
We use information you provide to improve, grow, and optimize our Services, including to maintain and verify the quality of our Services, develop new Games, products, and other services, and understand how our Services are being used, our customer base and purchasing trends, and the effectiveness of our marketing.
Personalisation
We use information to offer you recommendations and tailor our Services to your preferences. The personal information we collect and use for these purposes includes:
Personal information provided by you:
Contact information, including name, username, email address, avatar or profile picture
Demographic information, including your country
Payment information, collected by our third-party payment processors to complete a purchase or provided by you to our Customer Service
Information you provide when you register with a Service, including when you link a third-party account to your Inspired Square Profile or play via a third-party account (such as your Facebook account)
Information contained in your communications to us, including when you contact our customer service
Any information you provide by interacting with our Services (please note that some comments or information will also be visible to other users of our Services)
Customer service information, such as any issues you raise and their resolution
Location information (State or country level) of your device
Information of contacts that you supply to us, may be shared with our service providers. We do not sell or share such information
Personal information automatically collected:
Websites visited before and after you use a Service
Browser type and language
IP address
Hardware and software information
Gameplay data
Usage data
Crash Log data
We disclose this personal information to:
Various Group Companies which may use the personal information for their own marketing purposes
Service providers, including billing firms, customer service support, consultancies, Information technology providers, cybersecurity providers, payment processors, accounting, and auditing firms
Partners and licensees who provide you with goods or services you have requested, or create applications and websites that benefit our player community
Inspired Square also publicly displays certain personal information about you, including third-party account information and gameplay information, on our Services, or the properties operated by our third-party partners and licensees. For example, your Inspired Square Profile username will be displayed on leaderboards if you are a top player in one of our Games. If you have synced a third-party account with your Inspired Square Profile, we, or our third-party partners or licensees, will make your username available to be searched by other users if you have not opted out of this feature.
Promotions and Competitions
When Inspired Square runs promotions or competitions, we collect certain personal information from participants to enter them into the promotion and to deliver any prizes won. We will also need to collect additional information for you to claim a prize. We will combine that information with other information we have collected about you and use such combined information for other purposes stated in this Privacy Policy.
Advertising
We share your personal information, including name, email address, profile picture or avatar, and other in-game information, with our advertising partners and other third parties that provide us with advertising and marketing services, and social networks, including, but not limited to, Meta Platforms, Inc. (Facebook), Twitter, Inc. (Twitter), Google LLC (Google), and ByteDance Inc. (TikTok). These third parties may use such personal information to better target their advertisements and content to your interests and preferences. We may share your personal information with third parties who may use such personal information to identify you across platforms, devices, websites, and applications, and they may also share such personal information with other third parties for advertising and marketing purposes.
We also collect and use certain cookies and tracking technologies, including your IP address, advertising identifiers, and other unique identifiers, to personalize advertisements and to analyze our advertising campaigns and marketing efforts. These cookies and tracking technologies may be used by us and by our advertising partners to provide you with personalized advertisements and content, as well as to track the performance of our advertising campaigns and marketing efforts. You may opt out of targeted advertising and personalized content by following the instructions provided by the relevant advertising networks, platforms, and service providers. However, please note that if you opt out of targeted advertising, you may still see advertisements and content that are not personalized to your interests and preferences.
Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "last updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information. Your continued use of our Services after any changes to this Privacy Policy will signify your acceptance of those changes.
Additional Notes
You may choose to disclose data about yourself in the course of contributing user-generated content to the games.
Any data that you disclose in any of these forums, blogs, chats or the like will become public information, and there is no expectation of privacy or confidentiality with respect to that data.
Subscriptions
Payment will be charged to iTunes Account at confirmation of purchase.
Subscription automatically renews unless auto-renew is turned off at least 24-hours before the end of the current period.
Account will be charged for renewal within 24-hours prior to the end of the current period, and identify the cost of the renewal.
Subscriptions may be managed by the user and auto-renewal may be turned off by going to the user's Account Settings after purchase.
