Definitions
Group Companies:
means any company that is a parent, subsidiary, or affiliate of Inspired Square, or that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with Inspired Square.
Service Providers:
means third-party service providers that perform services on our behalf, such as payment processing, data analysis, customer service, email delivery, and hosting services.
Personal Information:
means any information that can be used to identify you, directly or indirectly, including but not limited to, your name, email address, IP address, and any other information that can be linked to you.
Cookies:
means small text files that are placed on your device when you visit a website, which are used to store information about your preferences and activity.
Ad Identifiers:
means unique identifiers that are used to identify your device for advertising purposes.
Third-Party Account:
means any account that you have with a third-party social network or platform, such as Facebook or Google, that you use to access our Services.
State Privacy Laws:
means privacy laws enacted by individual states within the United States, including but not limited to, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA), and other similar laws.
Targeted Advertising:
means advertising that is tailored to your interests and preferences based on information collected about you, including your browsing behavior, location, and other personal information.
Legal Basis:
means the lawful basis under which we process your personal information, including but not limited to, your consent, our legitimate interests, the performance of a contract, and compliance with legal obligations.
Retention Period:
means the length of time we retain your personal information for the purposes for which it was collected.
Consent Management Platform (CMP):
means a platform that collects and manages user consent for the use of cookies and other tracking technologies for advertising and other purposes.
Marketing Communications:
means communications that promote our Games and other Services, including emails, advertisements, and other marketing materials.
Personal Data Protection Laws:
means laws and regulations that govern the collection, use, and processing of personal information, including but not limited to, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and other similar laws.
Opt-In/Opt-Out:
means the process by which you can choose to consent to or decline the collection, use, and sharing of your personal information for specific purposes, such as marketing and targeted advertising.
By using our Services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the collection, use, and sharing of your personal information as described herein. If you do not agree to this Privacy Policy, please do not use our Services.
